text: Clonmel is an unincorporated community in Illinois Township, Sedgwick County, Kansas United States. ==History== Clonmel was a train station on the Kansas City, Mexico and Orient Railway. The first post office in Clonmel opened in 1905. It closed in 1938. It was named after Clonmel in Ireland. ==References== ==Other websites== * Sedgwick County Maps: Current , Historic , KDOT Category:Unincorporated communities in Sedgwick County, Kansas
